Parameter: File Name
Description: Serves as the ID for the scan

Parameter: Analysis eligibility
Description:
0 - Ineligible for analysis 
1- Eligible for analysis

Parameter: Number of Bscans
Description: Total number of Bscans

Parameter: Number of Bscans with Fluid
Description: Total number of Bscans with fluid

Parameter: SRF
Description:
0 - Absence of Sub Retinal Fluid
1 -Presence of Sub Retinal Fluid

Parameter: IRF
Description:
0 - Absence of Intra Retinal Fluid 
1 - Presence of Intra Retinal Fluid

Parameter: Fluid
Description:
0 - Absence of Fluid 
1 - Presence of Fluid

Parameter: SRF Volume
Description: Sum of the area of SRF regions multiplied by the distance between B-scans within the analyzed en-face area

Parameter: IRF Volume
Description: Sum of the area of IRF regions multiplied by the distance between B-scans within the analyzed en-face area

Parameter: TRF Volume
Description: Sum of the area of fluid regions multiplied by the distance between B-scans within the analyzed en-face area

Parameter: Average IRF height
Description: The average of the IRF fluid thickness within the analyzed en-face area

Parameter: Average SRF height
Description: The average of the SRF fluid thickness within the analyzed en-face area

Parameter: Average TRF height
Description: Sum of the average IRF height and the average SRF height

Parameter: Max IRF height
Description: The max of the IRF fluid thickness within the analyzed en-face area

Parameter: Max SRF height
Description: The max of the SRF fluid thickness within the analyzed en-face area

Parameter: B-scan with 1st largest area of fluid
Description:
The index number of the B-scan with the  highest total fluid area
-1000 - B-scan is not available

Parameter: B-scan with 2nd largest area of fluid
Description:
The index number of the B-scan with the second highest total fluid area
-1000 - B-scan is not available

Parameter: B-scan with 3rd largest area of fluid
Description:
The index number of the B-scan with the third highest total fluid area
-1000 - B-scan is not available

Parameter: Analyzed en-face area
Description: The net area analyzed by the algorithm

Parameter: Retinal volume
Description: The volume of the retina within the analyzed en-face area based on ILM to RPE delineation

Parameter: Average retinal height
Description: Retinal volume divided by the analyzed en-face area

Parameter: Vitrous-Macula Interface (VMI) abnormalities
Description:
Presence of hyporeflective regions that interface with the ILM which  are not classified as IRF  
0 - Absent 
1 - Present

Parameter: Vitrous-Macula Interface (VMI) abnormalities
Description: Volume of hyporeflective regions that interface with the ILM which  are not classified as IRF

Parameter: RPE irregularities
Description:
0 - Absence of drusen or PED
1 - Presence of drusen of PED

Parameter: Retinal pigment epithelial detachment (PED)
Description:
0 - Absence of PED 
1 - Presence of PED

Parameter: Volume of retinal pigment epithelial detachment (PED)
Description: Volume of retinal pigment epithelial detachment within the analyzed en-face area

Parameter: Volume of RPE irregularities
Description: Including drusen and PED, multiplied by the distance between B-scans within the analyzed en-face area

Parameter: Maximal height of RPE irregularities
Description: Including PED

Parameter: Average RPE irregularities height
Description: Dividing the volume of RPE irregularities by the analyzed en-face area

Parameter: Section with highest RPE irregularity (max height)
Description:
The index number of the B-scan with the highest PED or drusen
-1000 - B-scan is not available

Parameter: Section with the most evidence for RPE irregularities
Description:
The index number of the B scan with the highest classification score for RPE irregularities 
-1000 -  B-scan is not available
